  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed and a screening sensitivity exercise was conducted to rank input parameters by their contribution to hemolysis index variance. All 13 credibility factors are addressed: 7 assessed (achieved levels meet or exceed required levels after remediation) and 6 previously flagged as epistemic gaps now resolved through supplemental validation data. Decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v2",
