      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple independent experimental samples (n≥3 pump units) must be used to characterize unit-to-unit manufacturing variability in hemolysis measurements.",
      "rationale": "FDA dataset provides replicate measurements but from a single pump unit; inter-unit manufacturing variability is not characterized. Only one physical pump was tested across all five operating points. Achieved level 2 falls short of required level 4 — significant gap for Class III device assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Correspondence between experimental and simulation input parameters must be demonstrated quantitatively, including any surrogate fluid corrections.",
      "rationale": "Glycerol-water analogue used in experiments differs from whole blood in viscoelastic properties and red blood cell deformability. Correction factors applied for viscosity matching but no correction for non-Newtonian effects or RBC aggregation. Achieved level 2 falls short of required level 4 — equivalency gap at high-shear conditions."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite identified gaps in model form (factor 10, achieved 3 vs required 5), model inputs (factor 11, achieved 3 vs required 5), test samples (factor 12, achieved 2 vs required 4), and equivalency of input parameters (factor 13, achieved 2 vs required 4), the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ results — including a preliminary screening sensitivity analysis documented in project technical memoranda — demonstrate that hemolysis predictions remain below the clinical threshold even at the 95th percentile of the uncertainty distribution. The conservative bias observed in output comparison (over-prediction at 4 of 5 operating points) further supports patient safety. Remediation plan for model form and test sample gaps is documented for the next design iteration. Regulatory submission will include this credibility package with gap disclosures.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
